title: Tray, 1823–24
markings: London marks for 1823-24 and punched "EB" within a square shape.
dimensions: H x diam (must confirm): 9.4 x 65 cm (3 11/16 x 25 9/16 in.)
description: Broad cast ornamental border bearing marks, and figures and animals of ten classical hunt scenes among flowers and foliations. Four foliated feet terminate in dolphins' heads. Scroll and floral chasing. Engraved with impaled arms, crest, motto, ribbon and supporters of Fuller.
